        "title": "Biased NMOS — Channel Formation and Current Flow",
        "src": "/course/analog-electronics/lesson-09/nmos-biased-channel.png",
        "caption": "With VGS > VT applied, the induced n-channel connects source to drain. Conventional current ID flows from D to S (electrons flow S to D). Note: iG = 0 and iS = iD."
